<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 16 at 4:42PM EDT  by NWS Pittsburgh</headline>
<description>...A STRONG THUNDERSTORM WILL IMPACT SOUTHEASTERN HARRISON...SOUTHERN
JEFFERSON AND NORTH CENTRAL BELMONT COUNTIES THROUGH 515 PM EDT...
At 442 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
St. Clairsville, moving northeast at 40 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Steubenville, Cadiz, Wintersville, Mingo Junction, Hopedale,
Flushing, Smithfield, Adena, New Athens, New Alexandria, Harrisville,
and Bloomingdale.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
